I'm trying to parse a real-world C source code (QEMU) with pycparser. It chokes on function prototypes containing pointer to pointer params like this:

```
typedef struct Error {
    int dummy;
} Error;
void func_with_pp_param(const char *, Error **);
```

Adding a name to the last param, i.e.

`void func_with_pp_param(const char *, Error **p);`

makes the parsing magically work.

Any chances to get a support for such constructs in pycparser?

