https://github.com/mozilla-services/python-dockerflow/issues/8 fixes the exception that can happen when you log objects. What'd be even nicer, as @jezdez pointed out, would be to handle datetimes/dates : currently they are serialized as ` "datetime.datetime(2017, 4, 6, 9, 27, 7, 479427)"` because that's the `repr()` for a `datetime` object, but we could do better by using `DjangoJSONEncoder`, which knows how to handle those objects and more.

Something like this should work, to test:
```python
class SafeJSONEncoder(json.JSONEncoder):
    def default(self, o):
        return repr(o)

class SafeDjangoJSONEncoder(DjangoJSONEncoder, SafeJSONEncoder):
    pass
```

Then use `cls=SafeDjangoJSONEncoder` when doing the `json.dumps`.

